{"id":66012,"title":"Continence care for people with dementia at home.","abstract":"The majority of people with dementia live in their own homes. Difficulties with using the toilet and incontinence can lead to them moving into care homes. This report summarises a systematic review by Drennan et al (2012) that investigated the evidence for conservative interventions for the prevention or management of incontinence in people with dementia living at home.","date":"2014-04-23","categories":"Male Urogenital Diseases","split":"train","url":"http://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/24754106","annotations":[{"name":"Systematic review","weight":0.136645,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Systematic_review"},{"name":"Dementia","weight":0.102918,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Dementia"},{"name":"Preventive medicine","weight":0.0508378,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Preventive_medicine"},{"name":"Management","weight":0.0370044,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Management"},{"name":"Conservatism","weight":0.0346026,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Conservatism"},{"name":"Toilet","weight":0.0300804,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Toilet"},{"name":"Evidence","weight":0.0300804,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Evidence"},{"name":"Lead","weight":0.0279596,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Lead"},{"name":"Intervention (counseling)","weight":0.0168623,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Intervention_(counseling)"},{"name":"Nursing home","weight":0.0156704,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Nursing_home"},{"name":"Urinary incontinence","weight":0.0152908,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Urinary_incontinence"},{"name":"Systematics","weight":0.0147415,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Systematics"}]}
